CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, August 8, 1959, pg. B9 reads: "Frog Week Events Highlight Gay Social Season - Bicentennial Medallion - Jack Petrill of the Pittsburgh Bicentennial Festival presents a Bicentennial Medallion to Atty. Henry Smith, president of the Frog Club, during intermission at the formal last Friday. Looking on are veteran Frogs Harry Washington and Byron Peters St. The club was cited for its cultural contribution to the city's Bicentennial celebration. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Jack Petrill, holding microphone, standing next Atty. Henry R. Smith, with Harry Washington and Byron Peters Sr. in foreground, standing in Gateway Plaza ballroom for FROGS formal, another version
